\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
1.
 Purpose
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The purpose of this policy is to establish mandatory standards for all communications conducted by Elko County Information Operations personnel with end users,
 internal stakeholders,
 vendors,
 and external partners.
 Clear,
 professional,
 and documented communication is foundational to service accountability,
 operational continuity,
 and public trust in County IT operations.
 This policy ensures that all interactions —
 regardless of channel or audience —
 are traceable,
 appropriately scoped,
 and consistent with the Department's governance obligations.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
2.
 Scope
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
This policy applies to all Information Operations Department personnel,
 including the IT Director,
 Assistant IT Director,
 and all IT staff at every tier.
 It governs verbal,
 written,
 and electronic communications conducted in the performance of IT duties,
 including but not limited to:
 service request interactions with County end users and department heads;
 coordination with vendors and managed service providers;
 and communications with external partners acting on behalf of or in support of County IT operations.
 This policy does not govern security incident communications during active incident response;
 those communications are governed by 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:4.06"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
,
 with this policy providing foundational channel and documentation standards that apply during the pre-escalation and post-resolution phases.
\end_layout

